                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14093700" author="yukim" created="Tue, 12 Aug 2014 03:59:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think we have concurrency bug in CompactionManager that compactingCF count remains 1 when there is no active compaction.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;submitBackground&lt;/tt&gt; adds compacting CF to compactingCF and &lt;tt&gt;BackgroundCompactionTask&lt;/tt&gt; removes the same CF after compaction.&lt;br/&gt;
Currently this can happen in either order, and when remove happens first, compacting count remains 1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Attaching patch to fix this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;edit: Though it should continue to compact if further flushing happens and there is compaction thread available.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14095368" author="krummas" created="Wed, 13 Aug 2014 11:23:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14095591" author="yukim" created="Wed, 13 Aug 2014 15:35:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed, thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
